### ps command - view processes ####

# ps  options
-e          Everything
-f          Full format listing
-p pid      Display information for PID
-ef         Display all processes, full

# Display specific user's processes
ps -u  unsername   

# display ps as a tree (couple of ways to do it)
ps -eH   Display a process tree
ps -ef --forest   Display a process tree

# pipe to less 
ps -ef | less


### other ways to view processes ####
# pstree   Display processes in a tree format

# top      Interactive process viewer
displays processes using most CPU at top of the list
type ? for help

# htop     Interactive process viewer
same info as top but different format, not on RHEL


